1
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:06,988
QUEEN OF TEARS

2
00:01:07,697 --> 00:01:09,324
EPISODE 10

3
00:01:21,961 --> 00:01:23,088
Hey!

4
00:01:25,173 --> 00:01:26,633
QUEEN'S BOXING GYM

5
00:01:31,471 --> 00:01:33,306
You found the right place.

6
00:01:33,389 --> 00:01:36,726
This building has the best wi-fi in town.

7
00:01:36,810 --> 00:01:37,977
Come by whenever you want.

8
00:01:38,937 --> 00:01:40,271
Thank you.

9
00:01:40,355 --> 00:01:42,440
WINNER BOYS YOUTH GROUP, BAEK HYUN-WOO

10
00:01:43,983 --> 00:01:45,443
"Baek Hyun-woo"?

11
00:01:45,527 --> 00:01:47,445
Did he use to box?

12
00:01:47,529 --> 00:01:48,530
Yes.

13
00:01:49,114 --> 00:01:50,281
And he was good at it.

14
00:01:52,283 --> 00:01:55,245
He's so smart that he uses his brain when boxing.

15
00:01:55,328 --> 00:01:58,665
He predicts his opponent's movements.

16
00:02:05,130 --> 00:02:07,715
Simply put, he's a living simulator.

17
00:02:11,636 --> 00:02:13,972
He lures you in, then dodges your moves.

18
00:02:14,931 --> 00:02:20,395
He waits until you're exhausted, and then he lands his punches on you.

19
00:02:21,521 --> 00:02:22,564
You become powerless.

20
00:02:22,647 --> 00:02:24,399
He even knocked me out too.

21
00:02:29,737 --> 00:02:32,323
I couldn't locate you, so I couldn't send you the papers.

22
00:02:34,868 --> 00:02:36,077
Here you go.

23
00:02:36,911 --> 00:02:38,413
Make sure you hire an attorney.

24
00:02:39,330 --> 00:02:40,248
What?

25
00:02:40,331 --> 00:02:43,126
I called them before hopping out of my car.

26
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:49,716
You've been caught in the act, so you'll be taken to the station.

27
00:02:51,259 --> 00:02:53,469
POLICE FOR THE PEOPLE

28
00:02:57,724 --> 00:02:59,350
MR. YOON EUN-SUNG

29
00:03:01,019 --> 00:03:02,979
MR. PYEON

30
00:03:06,774 --> 00:03:07,609
Hyun-woo?

31
00:03:32,967 --> 00:03:36,012
Have you been lying low at your ex-husband's of all places?

32
00:03:36,095 --> 00:03:37,096
I'm disappointed.

33
00:03:37,180 --> 00:03:38,473
Disappointed?

34
00:03:38,556 --> 00:03:40,266
That's rich coming from you.

35
00:03:42,268 --> 00:03:43,353
How did you find me?

36
00:03:43,436 --> 00:03:46,981
You should know by now that I do anything I set my mind to.

37
00:03:47,065 --> 00:03:48,566
It was easy to find you.

38
00:03:49,192 --> 00:03:50,276
So, Hae-in.

39
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,819
Don't turn me any more evil.

40
00:03:55,281 --> 00:03:57,075
Are you threatening me?

41
00:03:57,158 --> 00:03:59,535
Yes, I am.

42
00:04:00,453 --> 00:04:02,830
But here comes the real threat, so listen up.

43
00:04:03,665 --> 00:04:05,083
I saw your doctor's diagnosis.

44
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:09,045
But your doctor refuses to elaborate

45
00:04:09,128 --> 00:04:10,463
since I'm not your guardian.

46
00:04:11,297 --> 00:04:12,465
So…

47
00:04:12,548 --> 00:04:13,925
I'm going to be just that.

48
00:04:14,842 --> 00:04:15,677
Are you crazy?

49
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,679
Yes, I think I am a little.

50
00:04:22,809 --> 00:04:24,269
I know you don't have much time.

51
00:04:25,687 --> 00:04:27,522
So I don't either, and that drives me nuts.

52
00:04:27,605 --> 00:04:29,065
I have nothing to fear.

53
00:04:31,192 --> 00:04:32,402
Fine, do as you please.

54
00:04:32,485 --> 00:04:34,028
I have nothing to fear either.

55
00:04:35,655 --> 00:04:37,657
Your parents don't know that you're ill.

56
00:04:39,784 --> 00:04:41,244
Why haven't you told them?

57
00:04:41,327 --> 00:04:42,495
Because you're scared.

58
00:04:43,454 --> 00:04:46,082
I understand. They already lost a son once.

59
00:04:50,336 --> 00:04:51,504
Hey, Eun-sung.

60
00:04:51,587 --> 00:04:53,047
Keep acting this way

61
00:04:53,673 --> 00:04:56,467
if you want me to make those you love miserable.

62
00:04:57,343 --> 00:04:58,344
If you don't,

63
00:04:59,137 --> 00:05:01,139
come back soon.

64
00:05:02,181 --> 00:05:04,058
Your position is still available.

65
00:05:04,142 --> 00:05:05,518
You have two days.

66
00:05:06,769 --> 00:05:08,438
I'll hold a press conference then.

67
00:05:08,521 --> 00:05:09,439
See you there.

68
00:05:12,984 --> 00:05:14,360
Leave it all up to me.

69
00:05:16,821 --> 00:05:18,323
The one who'll save you…

70
00:05:20,491 --> 00:05:21,576
is me, not Hyun-woo.

71
00:05:24,954 --> 00:05:26,539
You bastard!

72
00:05:27,665 --> 00:05:29,459
How could you do this to us?

73
00:05:29,542 --> 00:05:31,294
How could you do this to me?

74
00:05:31,377 --> 00:05:33,588
I'm going to kill you!

75
00:05:37,050 --> 00:05:38,301
Gosh, Soo-cheol.

76
00:05:42,764 --> 00:05:43,806
Hey, are you okay?

77
00:05:44,474 --> 00:05:47,393
Our family is ruined

78
00:05:47,477 --> 00:05:48,978
because I was fooled by you.

79
00:05:49,062 --> 00:05:49,896
I'm to blame.

80
00:05:52,982 --> 00:05:53,900
You idiot.

81
00:05:54,942 --> 00:05:56,361
It's not your fault.

82
00:05:56,444 --> 00:05:58,696
Anyone would've been deceived.

83
00:05:59,530 --> 00:06:01,366
It's not your fault, so stop crying.

84
00:06:04,118 --> 00:06:05,411
Where's Da-hye?

85
00:06:05,495 --> 00:06:06,913
Where is she?

86
00:06:08,164 --> 00:06:09,457
Just tell me

87
00:06:09,540 --> 00:06:11,834
if she's doing fine.

88
00:06:14,045 --> 00:06:15,254
Please.

89
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:37,193
You just tripped on a stone and fell

90
00:06:37,276 --> 00:06:38,778
while running in the dark.

91
00:06:38,861 --> 00:06:39,695
Why would I?

92
00:06:39,779 --> 00:06:41,364
Because you were drunk.

93
00:06:41,447 --> 00:06:42,698
I didn't drink.

94
00:06:44,325 --> 00:06:47,453
I'm saying the others shouldn't know that Eun-sung was here.

95
00:06:48,204 --> 00:06:49,288
Why was he here?

96
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:56,129
I should know why that bastard came here.

97
00:06:57,171 --> 00:06:58,172
There's something

98
00:06:59,173 --> 00:07:02,760
I need to do, so don't tell our parents just yet.

99
00:07:05,304 --> 00:07:06,681
Answer me.

100
00:07:08,266 --> 00:07:09,183
Fine.

101
00:07:11,018 --> 00:07:13,729
I have night blindness, so I couldn't see anything.

102
00:07:17,942 --> 00:07:20,111
You know I can catch mosquitoes in the dark.

103
00:07:20,194 --> 00:07:22,530
Yes, seeing in the dark is your sole talent.

104
00:07:22,613 --> 00:07:25,825
Exactly, and it was this guy.

105
00:07:25,908 --> 00:07:28,703
The new chairman of Queens.

106
00:07:28,786 --> 00:07:29,912
-Really? -Yeah.

107
00:07:29,996 --> 00:07:31,581
That means he's their sworn enemy.

108
00:07:31,664 --> 00:07:32,915
Exactly.

109
00:07:35,001 --> 00:07:36,252
What? Do you know him?

110
00:07:36,335 --> 00:07:37,336
He's my type.

111
00:07:54,187 --> 00:07:55,313
YOON EUN-SUNG

112
00:07:56,189 --> 00:07:57,023
Damn it.

113
00:07:57,982 --> 00:07:59,025
Took you long enough.

114
00:07:59,108 --> 00:08:02,111
Did you delete your Korean number, email, and social media?

115
00:08:02,195 --> 00:08:03,029
Of course.

116
00:08:03,112 --> 00:08:04,947
I'm moving in under a fake name too.

117
00:08:05,031 --> 00:08:06,032
Good.

118
00:08:06,115 --> 00:08:07,492
Let's not call each other.

119
00:08:07,575 --> 00:08:09,452
-Only call if it's urgent for now. -Okay.

120
00:08:10,703 --> 00:08:11,954
By the way,

121
00:08:12,747 --> 00:08:14,207
did you see Soo-cheol?

122
00:08:16,209 --> 00:08:17,210
Why?

123
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,212
No reason.

124
00:08:19,295 --> 00:08:20,880
He's very weak-minded.

125
00:08:20,963 --> 00:08:22,131
I'm sure he's shocked.

126
00:08:22,215 --> 00:08:23,966
So? Are you worried?

127
00:08:24,759 --> 00:08:26,636
Why would I be?

128
00:08:26,719 --> 00:08:28,304
I'm just curious. That's all.

129
00:08:28,930 --> 00:08:30,139
Soo-cheol…

130
00:08:32,141 --> 00:08:33,184
is furious at you.

131
00:08:35,269 --> 00:08:36,687
Is that so?

132
00:08:36,771 --> 00:08:39,440
He's going to make you pay if he finds you,

133
00:08:40,024 --> 00:08:41,275
so lie low.

134
00:08:41,359 --> 00:08:42,818
Okay. Bye.

135
00:08:47,323 --> 00:08:48,824
Of course, he's mad.

136
00:08:51,577 --> 00:08:52,620
I would be too.

137
00:08:54,664 --> 00:08:56,832
He's finally matured up.

138
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:58,876
He wasn't a complete fool after all.

139
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,878
Da-hye…

140
00:09:06,592 --> 00:09:08,219
Da-hye…

141
00:09:09,554 --> 00:09:11,097
Da-hye…

142
00:09:20,439 --> 00:09:21,691
BAEK HYUN-WOO

143
00:09:22,608 --> 00:09:24,110
The person you dialed is unavailable.

144
00:09:24,193 --> 00:09:27,196
Please leave a message after the beep. You may need to pay…

145
00:09:54,807 --> 00:09:55,933
What happened?

146
00:09:56,017 --> 00:09:57,977
You got off work hours ago, so why are you late?

147
00:09:58,060 --> 00:10:00,062
And what happened to your face?

148
00:10:00,146 --> 00:10:01,397
I just…

149
00:10:02,064 --> 00:10:03,024
Well…

150
00:10:06,068 --> 00:10:08,112
-Did you get hit? -No, I didn't.

151
00:10:09,155 --> 00:10:11,324
How badly hurt are you?

152
00:10:11,407 --> 00:10:13,200
Hae-in, let me explain.

153
00:10:13,284 --> 00:10:14,827
Hae-in. Please?

154
00:10:17,371 --> 00:10:19,624
Let me talk. Hold on. Let me--

155
00:10:21,751 --> 00:10:23,085
Stay still.

156
00:10:26,088 --> 00:10:27,757
Stop it.

157
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:29,467
Come here. Let me check.

158
00:10:32,261 --> 00:10:34,889
Why is this red? Did you get clubbed or something?

159
00:10:36,307 --> 00:10:37,308
Let me…

160
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:39,977
explain.

161
00:10:40,061 --> 00:10:41,729
I wasn't beaten up.

162
00:10:41,812 --> 00:10:43,189
Open your mouth.

163
00:10:47,151 --> 00:10:48,736
Did you bite your tongue?

164
00:10:49,236 --> 00:10:50,071
No.

165
00:10:50,946 --> 00:10:53,574
I didn't bite my tongue or get beaten up.

166
00:10:53,658 --> 00:10:56,202
Look. I'm perfectly fine.

167
00:10:57,620 --> 00:11:00,790
I just got some scratches and a split lip.

168
00:11:01,332 --> 00:11:02,583
And why exactly?

169
00:11:19,475 --> 00:11:20,351
Stay still.

170
00:11:26,649 --> 00:11:29,110
I'm not trying to brag,

171
00:11:29,193 --> 00:11:30,695
but I was up against three men.

172
00:11:32,530 --> 00:11:34,657
It wasn't an easy fight.

173
00:11:35,366 --> 00:11:36,617
And they

174
00:11:36,701 --> 00:11:38,035
even carried

175
00:11:38,119 --> 00:11:41,872
batons and other weapons when they came for me.

176
00:11:41,956 --> 00:11:43,290
And you weren't armed?

177
00:11:43,374 --> 00:11:44,750
Well…

178
00:11:44,834 --> 00:11:49,255
You probably didn't know, but I used to box when I was little.

179
00:11:49,338 --> 00:11:51,424
I can take blows well,

180
00:11:51,507 --> 00:11:53,426
so it didn't hurt one bit.

181
00:11:53,509 --> 00:11:54,468
Hold on.

182
00:11:56,929 --> 00:11:59,098
It just stung.

183
00:12:00,433 --> 00:12:02,977
Who was it? Which lunatic did this to you?

184
00:12:03,060 --> 00:12:05,020
Remember that land broker

185
00:12:05,646 --> 00:12:07,022
who's on the No Fly List?

186
00:12:07,106 --> 00:12:07,940
So…

187
00:12:08,607 --> 00:12:11,277
you were mobbed while tracking the scammer down?

188
00:12:12,361 --> 00:12:13,404
But I won.

189
00:12:14,530 --> 00:12:15,573
I'm not impressed.

190
00:12:16,657 --> 00:12:19,869
You should've run away if you were outnumbered.

191
00:12:19,952 --> 00:12:21,454
He was arrested though.

192
00:12:21,537 --> 00:12:24,915
We can turn the tables if he's proven guilty--

193
00:12:24,999 --> 00:12:25,833
Shut up.

194
00:12:32,965 --> 00:12:34,717
If this ever happens again,

195
00:12:35,468 --> 00:12:36,469
just run away.

196
00:12:37,178 --> 00:12:38,012
Promise me.

197
00:12:43,058 --> 00:12:43,976
Answer me.

198
00:12:44,977 --> 00:12:45,978
You said to shut up.

199
00:12:47,813 --> 00:12:49,231
But promise me.

200
00:12:52,777 --> 00:12:53,986
I'm sorry.

201
00:12:55,404 --> 00:12:56,489
I can't do that.

202
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:00,576
I've made a promise already.

203
00:13:01,702 --> 00:13:02,953
What promise?

204
00:13:04,955 --> 00:13:06,123
It's about you.

205
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:09,210
Anyway…

206
00:13:09,877 --> 00:13:11,378
It's a promise to myself.

207
00:13:16,008 --> 00:13:17,051
Don't make promises

208
00:13:18,135 --> 00:13:19,303
about me.

209
00:13:24,099 --> 00:13:26,352
Only married couples do that. And…

210
00:13:28,395 --> 00:13:30,523
We're divorced, so we don't have to.

211
00:13:46,288 --> 00:13:49,166
Come back beaten up like this again,

212
00:13:51,210 --> 00:13:52,670
and I'll kill you myself.

213
00:13:53,796 --> 00:13:54,880
Got that?

214
00:13:56,006 --> 00:13:57,466
I wasn't beaten--

215
00:14:00,302 --> 00:14:01,178
Okay.

216
00:14:16,819 --> 00:14:18,112
Let's eat.

217
00:14:25,870 --> 00:14:27,246
What happened to your face?

218
00:14:32,793 --> 00:14:33,794
I fell last night.

219
00:14:33,878 --> 00:14:35,004
What happened?

220
00:14:40,009 --> 00:14:41,927
Gosh, what happened to you?

221
00:14:44,638 --> 00:14:47,057
I tripped and fell.

222
00:14:47,141 --> 00:14:49,143
So you both fell?

223
00:14:49,226 --> 00:14:52,187
-Did you guys fight? -I wouldn't dare.

224
00:14:52,271 --> 00:14:53,397
I heard

225
00:14:54,023 --> 00:14:55,482
that he used to box.

226
00:14:56,525 --> 00:14:57,568
About that…

227
00:14:58,319 --> 00:14:59,153
So you heard.

228
00:14:59,236 --> 00:15:00,863
He visited my gym yesterday.

229
00:15:00,946 --> 00:15:02,823
He was shocked at your trophies.

230
00:15:02,907 --> 00:15:04,533
-I see. -Did you play sports?

231
00:15:05,451 --> 00:15:06,452
-Yes. -Gosh.

232
00:15:06,535 --> 00:15:10,372
I can finally say this now, but it wasn't easy raising him.

233
00:15:10,456 --> 00:15:12,958
He won every contest

234
00:15:13,042 --> 00:15:15,461
and was always in the top ten in the country

235
00:15:15,544 --> 00:15:18,255
after every exam.

236
00:15:18,339 --> 00:15:21,717
We didn't know which path to encourage him to take.

237
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,177
You're just perfect.

238
00:15:23,928 --> 00:15:27,097
-No. -It sounds like I'm bragging about my son.

239
00:15:27,848 --> 00:15:29,600
But it's the truth.

240
00:15:30,351 --> 00:15:33,270
He definitely took after me.

241
00:15:33,354 --> 00:15:36,649
No, Hyeon-tae is the one who took after you.

242
00:15:36,732 --> 00:15:39,735
Everyone said Hyun-woo was the odd member of our family.

243
00:15:39,818 --> 00:15:42,488
I take after my mom, so I can't lie.

244
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:48,827
What about you?

245
00:15:48,911 --> 00:15:50,788
He doesn't take after me.

246
00:15:52,373 --> 00:15:54,208
Why not? Of course, I do.

247
00:16:00,464 --> 00:16:02,174
As for Hae-in,

248
00:16:02,257 --> 00:16:05,094
she's beautiful

249
00:16:05,177 --> 00:16:07,054
just like her mother.

250
00:16:23,779 --> 00:16:24,905
Hyun-woo.

251
00:16:26,407 --> 00:16:27,324
What is it?

252
00:16:27,408 --> 00:16:28,742
Actually…

253
00:16:29,576 --> 00:16:32,705
Hae-in told me not to tell you but--

254
00:16:32,788 --> 00:16:33,872
About what?

255
00:16:40,587 --> 00:16:41,630
-What? -What?

256
00:16:41,714 --> 00:16:43,465
You had something to say.

257
00:16:43,549 --> 00:16:44,842
-Did I? -No?

258
00:16:46,427 --> 00:16:47,553
I thought you did.

259
00:16:48,303 --> 00:16:49,555
Go on, then.

260
00:16:55,394 --> 00:16:56,395
What's with him?

261
00:16:57,354 --> 00:16:58,439
Ignore him.

262
00:17:00,232 --> 00:17:02,109
Have you applied ointment this morning?

263
00:17:03,444 --> 00:17:05,946
No, I was in a rush.

264
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:07,781
Let me see your face.

265
00:17:22,337 --> 00:17:25,632
-You need to apply this often. -But I'm okay now.

266
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:27,926
No, you're not.

267
00:17:28,010 --> 00:17:30,095
Apply ointment

268
00:17:33,265 --> 00:17:35,392
and replace the bandage often, so it won't scar.

269
00:17:49,073 --> 00:17:49,907
There.

270
00:17:50,616 --> 00:17:51,700
Go.

271
00:17:51,784 --> 00:17:52,618
Okay.

272
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:56,121
All right, then.

273
00:17:57,998 --> 00:17:59,291
I'll be leaving now.

274
00:18:00,667 --> 00:18:01,502
Okay.

275
00:18:02,669 --> 00:18:04,671
Drive safely.

276
00:18:37,162 --> 00:18:37,996
What is it?

277
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:43,377
It's rush hour right now,

278
00:18:45,087 --> 00:18:46,964
so I think I should wait

279
00:18:47,756 --> 00:18:48,590
five minutes.

280
00:18:52,219 --> 00:18:53,220
Well…

281
00:18:53,554 --> 00:18:55,806
It's always best to avoid traffic.

282
00:18:57,724 --> 00:18:59,560
Yes, exactly.

283
00:19:01,728 --> 00:19:02,563
Right.

284
00:19:12,489 --> 00:19:15,075
YONGDU-RI SUPERMARKET

285
00:19:37,139 --> 00:19:38,807
What if we had done just that?

286
00:19:40,767 --> 00:19:41,602
What do you mean?

287
00:19:41,685 --> 00:19:44,104
If we had applied ointment on time,

288
00:19:44,188 --> 00:19:45,522
disinfected our wounds,

289
00:19:45,606 --> 00:19:47,608
and replaced our bandages every time,

290
00:19:48,358 --> 00:19:50,110
would things have been different?

291
00:19:52,779 --> 00:19:53,780
No, before that.

292
00:19:54,740 --> 00:19:55,991
What if we had broken up

293
00:19:56,074 --> 00:19:58,410
around the time when we had ice cream

294
00:19:58,493 --> 00:19:59,411
right here?

295
00:20:00,829 --> 00:20:03,749
If we hadn't gotten married, we would've cherished

296
00:20:04,458 --> 00:20:07,252
the memories even to this day.

297
00:20:08,295 --> 00:20:09,963
There would've been no need

298
00:20:10,047 --> 00:20:11,757
for wounds

299
00:20:12,591 --> 00:20:14,092
to fester

300
00:20:15,010 --> 00:20:16,428
or scars to form.

301
00:20:16,929 --> 00:20:18,180
You'd have met someone

302
00:20:18,639 --> 00:20:22,517
who was kinder, warmer,

303
00:20:23,310 --> 00:20:25,604
and better than me.

304
00:20:26,438 --> 00:20:28,649
You'd be happily living together.

305
00:20:29,691 --> 00:20:30,901
Probably not.

306
00:20:33,612 --> 00:20:35,405
If we had broken up,

307
00:20:35,489 --> 00:20:36,323
you probably

308
00:20:36,949 --> 00:20:38,784
wouldn't have known how I was doing.

309
00:20:39,618 --> 00:20:43,121
But I would've known what you were up to.

310
00:20:43,205 --> 00:20:44,039
And I probably

311
00:20:45,082 --> 00:20:46,792
would've been regretful.

312
00:20:48,752 --> 00:20:50,837
But if you knew how things would end up--

313
00:20:50,921 --> 00:20:52,005
Even still,

314
00:20:54,508 --> 00:20:56,009
I would've made the same choice.

315
00:21:01,932 --> 00:21:04,685
But had I known then what I know now,

316
00:21:04,768 --> 00:21:06,895
I would've asked you more often.

317
00:21:06,979 --> 00:21:07,813
Ask what?

318
00:21:08,438 --> 00:21:09,773
How your day went.

319
00:21:15,529 --> 00:21:16,405
"Is there anything

320
00:21:17,322 --> 00:21:18,323
that's troubling you?"

321
00:21:20,033 --> 00:21:21,201
I regret

322
00:21:21,868 --> 00:21:23,870
not asking you such questions.

323
00:22:17,090 --> 00:22:19,176
What time did you come home last night?

324
00:22:21,219 --> 00:22:22,846
Is the chairman okay?

325
00:22:29,311 --> 00:22:30,395
I understand

326
00:22:30,479 --> 00:22:32,105
what you mean.

327
00:22:32,856 --> 00:22:34,232
But first,

328
00:22:34,316 --> 00:22:35,901
bring the chairman back.

329
00:22:36,401 --> 00:22:37,986
Then we can discuss.

330
00:22:38,070 --> 00:22:39,154
We don't need to.

331
00:22:40,489 --> 00:22:43,116
I'm going to marry Hae-in as soon as I can.

332
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,326
What? Marry her?

333
00:22:46,870 --> 00:22:48,372
Did she agree to it?

334
00:22:48,872 --> 00:22:50,248
Do you still not know me?

335
00:22:52,626 --> 00:22:53,835
I'll make it happen.

336
00:23:07,933 --> 00:23:09,684
INTRANET

337
00:23:10,811 --> 00:23:13,772
NEW PERSONNEL APPOINTMENT

338
00:23:15,732 --> 00:23:17,901
BAEK HYUN-WOO REMOVAL FROM POSITION DUE TO MALPRACTICE

339
00:23:20,362 --> 00:23:21,238
Did you read it?

340
00:23:24,074 --> 00:23:25,283
What's going on?

341
00:23:26,034 --> 00:23:26,993
Is something up?

342
00:23:53,937 --> 00:23:55,397
It's smaller than I thought.

343
00:23:58,775 --> 00:24:00,652
It's just right for one person.

344
00:24:01,194 --> 00:24:03,864
You must be shocked by the sudden announcement.

345
00:24:05,282 --> 00:24:06,908
I did somewhat see it coming.

346
00:24:07,492 --> 00:24:08,618
But…

347
00:24:09,411 --> 00:24:10,245
"malpractice"?

348
00:24:10,328 --> 00:24:11,705
Do you have proof?

349
00:24:11,788 --> 00:24:14,416
Of course. A personnel committee will be scheduled soon.

350
00:24:14,499 --> 00:24:15,584
Find out for yourself then.

351
00:24:18,295 --> 00:24:19,129
I was surprised.

352
00:24:19,838 --> 00:24:20,839
Yongdu-ri, was it?

353
00:24:21,506 --> 00:24:22,507
The air was fresh.

354
00:24:23,675 --> 00:24:26,511
Even still, how could you take her there?

355
00:24:31,266 --> 00:24:33,226
I guess you didn't hear.

356
00:24:37,397 --> 00:24:38,773
I saw her yesterday.

357
00:24:40,358 --> 00:24:41,485
Did she not tell you?

358
00:24:42,611 --> 00:24:43,862
We had no time.

359
00:24:45,071 --> 00:24:46,281
I was quite busy.

360
00:24:46,364 --> 00:24:48,033
Mr. Pyeon was arrested yesterday.

361
00:24:50,619 --> 00:24:51,620
I see.

362
00:24:52,329 --> 00:24:53,622
I guess you didn't hear.

363
00:24:55,123 --> 00:24:56,500
I don't understand.

364
00:24:56,583 --> 00:24:59,669
From what I heard,

365
00:24:59,753 --> 00:25:01,421
he's also feigning ignorance right now.

366
00:25:01,505 --> 00:25:03,673
But don't worry. I have a knack

367
00:25:04,883 --> 00:25:06,635
for revealing truths.

368
00:25:11,932 --> 00:25:12,974
Is that so?

369
00:25:13,475 --> 00:25:14,476
Good.

370
00:25:15,143 --> 00:25:16,978
Let's do what we do best then.

371
00:25:19,689 --> 00:25:20,524
Bye.

372
00:25:44,047 --> 00:25:45,549
Shouldn't we say hi?

373
00:25:45,632 --> 00:25:48,969
Let's not. He's like Crown Prince Sado in that rice chest.

374
00:25:49,052 --> 00:25:50,971
-What do you mean? -Didn't you watch the movie?

375
00:25:51,054 --> 00:25:52,264
Instead of firing him,

376
00:25:52,347 --> 00:25:55,475
they placed him in front of everyone to see.

377
00:25:55,559 --> 00:25:58,019
They want to see who's on his side.

378
00:25:58,103 --> 00:26:00,397
Jeez, is that why they put him next to the smoking room?

379
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:02,899
They want to see who he's close with.

380
00:26:03,733 --> 00:26:04,568
Let's go.

381
00:26:15,036 --> 00:26:17,330
I didn't think you'd pick up my call.

382
00:26:19,583 --> 00:26:20,584
Right.

383
00:26:21,334 --> 00:26:24,838
I don't delete numbers that haven't been settled yet.

384
00:26:24,921 --> 00:26:28,383
There are always those who refuse to pay the matchmaking fee.

385
00:26:28,466 --> 00:26:32,554
I chase them to the ends of the earth and make sure they suffer.

386
00:26:33,263 --> 00:26:35,599
That's my way of settling things.

387
00:26:39,853 --> 00:26:41,730
Yes, I know.

388
00:26:41,813 --> 00:26:44,274
But I'm pretty precise about my settlements.

389
00:26:44,357 --> 00:26:45,275
What?

390
00:26:45,358 --> 00:26:49,279
Maybe you didn't get what you wanted because you didn't earn it.

391
00:26:49,362 --> 00:26:51,990
Are you saying I didn't do my job?

392
00:26:52,073 --> 00:26:56,202
Did you dedicate decades of your life and slave away under this roof?

393
00:26:56,286 --> 00:26:59,831
Or did you live abroad alone for many years like Eun-sung?

394
00:26:59,914 --> 00:27:02,542
It's not like you worked for free either.

395
00:27:02,626 --> 00:27:03,877
So I'm a bit dumbfounded

396
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:06,463
that you demanded to be the CEO after doing a few chores.

397
00:27:06,546 --> 00:27:10,133
Even still, you're telling me to go abroad

398
00:27:10,216 --> 00:27:11,051
with little money.

399
00:27:11,635 --> 00:27:12,802
Isn't that too harsh?

400
00:27:12,886 --> 00:27:14,804
I'll let you be the CEO then.

401
00:27:16,097 --> 00:27:17,641
But do your money's worth.

402
00:27:19,434 --> 00:27:20,435
How?

403
00:27:23,563 --> 00:27:24,689
Find Hong Man-dae.

404
00:27:24,773 --> 00:27:25,607
What?

405
00:27:26,274 --> 00:27:27,275
What do you…

406
00:27:40,497 --> 00:27:43,750
There aren't many hospitals that are fully staffed around the clock

407
00:27:43,833 --> 00:27:45,960
and have a VVIP room

408
00:27:46,044 --> 00:27:48,546
that covers an entire floor.

409
00:27:49,464 --> 00:27:51,091
All right. Let's begin.

410
00:27:51,174 --> 00:27:52,300
Okay.

411
00:27:53,385 --> 00:27:54,469
Hello.

412
00:27:54,552 --> 00:27:56,805
Is this the VIP room administration at Hanju Hospital?

413
00:27:56,888 --> 00:28:00,350
Our CEO wants to receive stem cell therapy.

414
00:28:00,433 --> 00:28:03,395
Is your VIP room on the 23rd floor available?

415
00:28:03,478 --> 00:28:05,063
What? He did what to my father?

416
00:28:06,856 --> 00:28:09,317
Where did he take him?

417
00:28:09,401 --> 00:28:10,652
I'm still looking into it.

418
00:28:10,735 --> 00:28:13,238
According to the nurse, Seul-hee wasn't involved.

419
00:28:13,321 --> 00:28:15,323
Eun-sung did it single-handedly.

420
00:28:15,407 --> 00:28:16,533
Damn it.

421
00:28:16,616 --> 00:28:18,702
I'm going to make them pay.

422
00:28:18,785 --> 00:28:20,620
You wait. I called a taxi.

423
00:28:20,704 --> 00:28:22,330
I'll be in Seoul soon.

424
00:28:24,582 --> 00:28:25,583
I'm hanging up.

425
00:28:26,710 --> 00:28:28,628
Hey, you're my mom's daughter.

426
00:28:29,587 --> 00:28:31,673
She tricked me that day.

427
00:28:31,756 --> 00:28:33,299
I was meaning to return this.

428
00:28:34,509 --> 00:28:35,343
Here.

429
00:28:36,553 --> 00:28:39,097
Your mother lent it to me that day.

430
00:28:39,180 --> 00:28:40,014
But…

431
00:28:40,765 --> 00:28:42,058
why did she?

432
00:28:42,142 --> 00:28:43,101
So that…

433
00:28:44,018 --> 00:28:46,730
I could wipe off what I had spilled.

434
00:28:46,813 --> 00:28:48,064
What did you spill?

435
00:28:56,406 --> 00:28:57,490
Why are you crying?

436
00:28:57,574 --> 00:28:58,742
Well…

437
00:29:02,287 --> 00:29:04,164
Gosh, I almost told you.

438
00:29:04,247 --> 00:29:05,665
What's it to you?

439
00:29:05,749 --> 00:29:07,542
Anyway, give that back to her.

440
00:29:08,960 --> 00:29:11,880
Only the biggest fools cry when times are tough.

441
00:29:12,964 --> 00:29:14,257
What did you say?

442
00:29:14,340 --> 00:29:16,050
I didn't cry.

443
00:29:16,134 --> 00:29:17,927
And only the average fools endure it.

444
00:29:19,262 --> 00:29:21,890
Then what do the wisest do?

445
00:29:23,266 --> 00:29:26,227
They eat meat when times are tough.

446
00:29:31,566 --> 00:29:35,111
Next time, have meat instead of crying like a fool.

447
00:29:44,954 --> 00:29:46,456
What is he saying?

448
00:29:47,040 --> 00:29:49,000
Meat, my foot.

449
00:29:52,003 --> 00:29:54,631
Jeez, this town is so weird.

450
00:29:56,883 --> 00:29:58,468
VILLAGE HEAD

451
00:30:13,107 --> 00:30:14,776
Looking good, Du-gwan.

452
00:30:16,361 --> 00:30:17,445
Why are you guys here?

453
00:30:17,529 --> 00:30:19,781
We're seeing you off for the last time.

454
00:30:20,532 --> 00:30:21,699
Hey.

455
00:30:21,783 --> 00:30:23,284
Am I dying or something?

456
00:30:30,458 --> 00:30:32,460
I'm Park Seok-hun, the new village head.

457
00:30:32,544 --> 00:30:34,796
INAUGURATION OF PARK SEOK-HUN, THE NEW VILLAGE HEAD

458
00:30:34,879 --> 00:30:37,549
It's a great day today. Enjoy yourselves.

459
00:30:37,632 --> 00:30:39,300
The inauguration party will take place

460
00:30:39,384 --> 00:30:41,427
at my pork and rice soup restaurant.

461
00:30:41,511 --> 00:30:44,347
Please come by and have some. I promise to do well!

462
00:30:44,430 --> 00:30:46,015
Please watch me!

463
00:30:48,268 --> 00:30:53,690
-Park Seok-hun! -Park Seok-hun!

464
00:30:53,773 --> 00:30:54,983
Let's go eat.

465
00:30:58,278 --> 00:30:59,112
By the way,

466
00:30:59,904 --> 00:31:01,322
where's Chun-sik?

467
00:31:03,241 --> 00:31:04,701
She's his daughter.

468
00:31:04,784 --> 00:31:08,413
We know everyone in this town. Should we have hired foreigners?

469
00:31:08,496 --> 00:31:09,831
And last time…

470
00:31:12,542 --> 00:31:13,751
Tell me in detail.

471
00:31:13,835 --> 00:31:15,920
What did Seok-hun's men say to you?

472
00:31:16,004 --> 00:31:18,882
Remember we went drinking during the farm succession gathering?

473
00:31:18,965 --> 00:31:21,134
And the receipt went missing.

474
00:31:21,801 --> 00:31:23,595
-That's why? -That's not all.

475
00:31:23,678 --> 00:31:25,513
They also brought all the part-time resumes

476
00:31:25,597 --> 00:31:28,683
from the urban-rural bazaar two years ago

477
00:31:28,766 --> 00:31:31,519
and claimed the part-timers were chosen out of favor.

478
00:31:31,603 --> 00:31:33,563
I can't believe them.

479
00:31:33,646 --> 00:31:35,732
Calm down.

480
00:31:37,066 --> 00:31:39,861
There are two things that don't exist in this world.

481
00:31:40,486 --> 00:31:41,779
One, freebies.

482
00:31:41,863 --> 00:31:43,656
Two,

483
00:31:43,740 --> 00:31:45,116
a peaceful transfer of power.

484
00:31:45,199 --> 00:31:48,077
That's true, Du-gwan.

485
00:31:48,161 --> 00:31:50,413
Those are worldwide facts.

486
00:31:50,496 --> 00:31:53,458
They're doing what they all do.

487
00:31:53,541 --> 00:31:55,126
When a new power takes over,

488
00:31:55,209 --> 00:31:58,296
they torment those closest to the previous one.

489
00:32:00,924 --> 00:32:02,342
Goodness.

490
00:32:02,425 --> 00:32:04,093
That's not all.

491
00:32:04,177 --> 00:32:07,639
They'll be erasing all traces of the previous regime soon.

492
00:32:09,015 --> 00:32:10,141
Erasing traces?

493
00:32:13,853 --> 00:32:16,689
Paint more. I can still see it. Here, use this.

494
00:32:16,773 --> 00:32:17,857
-Okay. -Okay.

495
00:32:17,941 --> 00:32:18,858
-Thank you. -Sure.

496
00:32:20,526 --> 00:32:23,863
VILLAGE HEAD

497
00:32:23,947 --> 00:32:24,948
Seok-hun.

498
00:32:25,031 --> 00:32:26,741
The pears are innocent.

499
00:32:26,824 --> 00:32:27,659
What?

500
00:32:27,742 --> 00:32:30,119
What you want to erase aren't those pears.

501
00:32:30,203 --> 00:32:33,122
It's my presence in this village.

502
00:32:33,206 --> 00:32:36,459
You want to erase my reputation as the wisest village head.

503
00:32:36,542 --> 00:32:37,752
That's not true.

504
00:32:37,835 --> 00:32:40,129
Yongdu-ri's new catchphrase will be

505
00:32:40,213 --> 00:32:42,674
"The Pretty Apple Village."

506
00:32:42,757 --> 00:32:44,300
So we need to draw them.

507
00:32:44,384 --> 00:32:47,220
There are tons of walls around here.

508
00:32:47,303 --> 00:32:50,139
Did you have to use this one?

509
00:32:50,223 --> 00:32:53,142
We're not asking you to treat us as if we're still in power.

510
00:32:53,226 --> 00:32:55,561
Just treat us with some respect.

511
00:32:57,647 --> 00:32:59,565
Are you going to keep watching?

512
00:33:00,984 --> 00:33:02,235
It's uncomfortable.

513
00:33:14,330 --> 00:33:15,623
INBOX

514
00:33:15,707 --> 00:33:17,417
UNDELIVERED DA-HYE

515
00:33:49,115 --> 00:33:50,324
Where are you?

516
00:33:50,408 --> 00:33:52,410
-I'm behind the tree. -I see.

517
00:33:55,621 --> 00:33:57,415
Thanks, honey. You saved me.

518
00:33:57,498 --> 00:33:58,499
Stay focused.

519
00:33:58,583 --> 00:34:01,377
-Use your poisoned darts. -I have none. I only have a hatchet.

520
00:34:01,461 --> 00:34:04,881
I told you to upgrade your weapons when you get money.

521
00:34:04,964 --> 00:34:06,382
Who uses a hatchet nowadays?

522
00:34:06,466 --> 00:34:08,009
Even a Vulcan isn't enough.

523
00:34:08,092 --> 00:34:09,093
I don't have any money.

524
00:34:09,177 --> 00:34:12,764
I need to hunt to get some, but I've been too busy to go hunting.

525
00:34:16,726 --> 00:34:17,935
Look behind you.

526
00:34:18,019 --> 00:34:20,605
You keep getting hit because you only look ahead.

527
00:34:20,688 --> 00:34:23,524
You see, they come from the front when I look back.

528
00:34:23,608 --> 00:34:24,776
Look behind you!

529
00:34:29,238 --> 00:34:31,240
Are you mad that I'm bad at this?

530
00:34:32,325 --> 00:34:35,286
We live in a dog-eat-dog world,

531
00:34:35,369 --> 00:34:37,580
so you have to be more cautious.

532
00:34:52,553 --> 00:34:54,222
FRIEND LIST GEONUMAMA

533
00:34:56,015 --> 00:34:56,933
What's the matter?

534
00:34:59,602 --> 00:35:01,187
OFFLINE 2 HOURS, 3 MINUTES, 4 SECONDS

535
00:35:03,189 --> 00:35:04,607
Da-hye…

536
00:35:07,568 --> 00:35:08,945
was online two hours ago.

537
00:35:11,489 --> 00:35:12,490
Thank you so much.

538
00:35:12,573 --> 00:35:13,991
Seriously. Thank you.

539
00:35:15,493 --> 00:35:16,786
Thank you so much.

540
00:35:16,869 --> 00:35:18,204
Go home safely, ma'am.

541
00:35:18,287 --> 00:35:19,580
Bye.

542
00:35:25,545 --> 00:35:26,546
Hello, ma'am.

543
00:35:27,130 --> 00:35:30,007
I just met with the Sama Medical Center director's wife.

544
00:35:30,842 --> 00:35:36,097
Chairman Ryu Seong-gwang's mistress is at their VIP room.

545
00:35:36,180 --> 00:35:38,724
She's resting after getting her breasts done--

546
00:35:43,271 --> 00:35:44,480
Yes.

547
00:35:45,189 --> 00:35:47,775
Okay. I'll call you back later.

548
00:35:51,070 --> 00:35:52,905
What brings you here?

549
00:36:01,873 --> 00:36:04,125
I remember you telling me that you knew little

550
00:36:04,750 --> 00:36:05,877
about legal matters

551
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:09,589
since you've been in the beauty industry and matchmaking wealthy families

552
00:36:10,339 --> 00:36:11,632
all your life.

553
00:36:14,218 --> 00:36:16,053
-So? -So I'm here to tell you something.

554
00:36:16,137 --> 00:36:17,471
You're managing

555
00:36:17,555 --> 00:36:21,184
thirteen unregistered branches of your spa.

556
00:36:21,267 --> 00:36:22,476
You shouldn't do that.

557
00:36:23,686 --> 00:36:25,021
Look.

558
00:36:25,104 --> 00:36:28,316
You're nitpicking over the fact that I worked harder than others.

559
00:36:28,399 --> 00:36:29,859
That hurts my feelings.

560
00:36:29,942 --> 00:36:33,404
Not only did you work hard, but you also dodged a hefty sum of taxes.

561
00:36:33,487 --> 00:36:35,990
Gosh, how much tax is all this?

562
00:36:36,073 --> 00:36:37,325
How much--

563
00:36:37,408 --> 00:36:39,744
By the way, who are you?

564
00:36:39,827 --> 00:36:40,828
Right.

565
00:36:44,790 --> 00:36:45,750
This is me.

566
00:36:47,168 --> 00:36:48,002
ATTORNEY KIM YANG-GI

567
00:36:48,085 --> 00:36:49,420
Ms. Ko.

568
00:36:49,503 --> 00:36:53,799
You're like a celebrity in our field, so I'm a bit starstruck right now.

569
00:36:53,883 --> 00:36:56,260
Why am I famous?

570
00:36:56,344 --> 00:36:59,597
Because you're an excellent matchmaker and homewrecker.

571
00:36:59,680 --> 00:37:02,266
You'd do everything in your power to split couples up

572
00:37:02,350 --> 00:37:04,018
if they didn't pay you well.

573
00:37:04,101 --> 00:37:07,188
You'd make false reports anonymously and hire people to seduce them.

574
00:37:07,271 --> 00:37:10,733
Thanks to you, I got some work.

575
00:37:10,816 --> 00:37:12,401
These are all the clients

576
00:37:13,027 --> 00:37:14,654
at our firm.

577
00:37:15,905 --> 00:37:18,407
This has nothing to do with you, so why do you care?

578
00:37:18,491 --> 00:37:20,159
These divorced couples

579
00:37:20,243 --> 00:37:24,080
won't sit still if they find out the truth.

580
00:37:24,163 --> 00:37:27,291
They're all hot-tempered

581
00:37:27,375 --> 00:37:29,377
and from influential backgrounds.

582
00:37:29,460 --> 00:37:31,879
The National Assembly, Prosecutors' Office, the court…

583
00:37:32,630 --> 00:37:33,631
Goodness.

584
00:37:34,507 --> 00:37:36,425
This chairman

585
00:37:36,509 --> 00:37:38,261
was a former gangster.

586
00:37:39,679 --> 00:37:41,681
I get it, so be quiet.

587
00:37:42,807 --> 00:37:44,308
Why are you doing this?

588
00:37:44,392 --> 00:37:47,311
I was on your side deep down.

589
00:37:47,395 --> 00:37:49,897
Then you should prove it.

590
00:37:55,820 --> 00:37:57,071
But you see…

591
00:37:57,738 --> 00:37:59,323
Sentiments don't move me.

592
00:38:00,992 --> 00:38:02,410
Only cash does.

593
00:38:02,493 --> 00:38:03,577
I'll be honest.

594
00:38:03,661 --> 00:38:07,832
They offered me a wonderful deal, so I'm hesitant to refuse it.

595
00:38:08,708 --> 00:38:12,837
So first, let me see what you can offer--

596
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:13,879
Damn it!

597
00:38:14,630 --> 00:38:16,382
You have no right to bargain.

598
00:38:16,465 --> 00:38:18,050
Are you a calculator?

599
00:38:18,134 --> 00:38:19,552
You're very quick-thinking.

600
00:38:19,635 --> 00:38:21,887
How could you think of striking a deal?

601
00:38:21,971 --> 00:38:22,847
Jeez.

602
00:38:22,930 --> 00:38:24,223
That's so harsh.

603
00:38:24,932 --> 00:38:27,893
Don't compare me to an object.

604
00:38:33,357 --> 00:38:37,111
You know me, right? I never hesitate to get my hands dirty.

605
00:38:38,779 --> 00:38:41,240
Quit calculating unless you want to go to prison.

606
00:38:41,324 --> 00:38:42,825
Speaking from experience,

607
00:38:42,908 --> 00:38:45,453
you're the type those ladies

608
00:38:45,536 --> 00:38:46,954
hate the most.

609
00:38:59,592 --> 00:39:02,678
Yoon Eun-sung is very thorough.

610
00:39:02,762 --> 00:39:05,389
There was nothing on the dashcam.

611
00:39:05,473 --> 00:39:08,684
I came up with a list of high-level general hospitals

612
00:39:08,768 --> 00:39:12,855
that allow security guards and have VIP rooms with private elevators

613
00:39:12,938 --> 00:39:14,857
where you can rent out an entire floor.

614
00:39:14,940 --> 00:39:17,651
-I've been looking into them. -So? Did you find him?

615
00:39:18,903 --> 00:39:20,613
It'll take a few days.

616
00:39:21,947 --> 00:39:25,534
I think we should search within an hour driving radius from Seoul.

617
00:39:25,618 --> 00:39:26,869
Why?

618
00:39:26,952 --> 00:39:28,412
Chairman Hong is critically ill.

619
00:39:28,496 --> 00:39:30,498
Most ambulances don't have oxygen tanks,

620
00:39:30,581 --> 00:39:33,501
which means the medical team must've had to manually give him oxygen.

621
00:39:33,584 --> 00:39:35,920
They could've only done that for an hour.

622
00:39:36,003 --> 00:39:37,338
Yes, that's plausible.

623
00:39:38,422 --> 00:39:40,716
Then that rules out five of these.

624
00:39:40,800 --> 00:39:43,844
I'll ask around and check the rest.

625
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:47,014
Let's share the list and look into it too.

626
00:39:47,098 --> 00:39:48,766
Yes, ma'am.

627
00:39:48,849 --> 00:39:51,352
You're like a family.

628
00:39:51,435 --> 00:39:53,187
I'm loving this vibe.

629
00:39:53,270 --> 00:39:55,815
The other side wasn't friendly at all.

630
00:40:01,153 --> 00:40:03,781
Do you think I was happy to kick you out?

631
00:40:03,864 --> 00:40:06,075
How have you all been?

632
00:40:07,493 --> 00:40:09,412
How is Ms. Kim doing?

633
00:40:09,495 --> 00:40:10,746
Wait.

634
00:40:12,206 --> 00:40:14,583
I'm sorry, Mi-seon. I should just leave.

635
00:40:14,667 --> 00:40:16,919
Goodness, we're already here though.

636
00:40:17,002 --> 00:40:19,463
They're all in there and waiting to apologize.

637
00:40:19,547 --> 00:40:21,674
I already know what they're going to say.

638
00:40:21,757 --> 00:40:23,926
"We didn't know you were present."

639
00:40:24,009 --> 00:40:27,263
"We weren't trying to hurt you. We're sorry."

640
00:40:27,346 --> 00:40:29,306
We didn't know you were here.

641
00:40:29,390 --> 00:40:31,934
We weren't trying to offend you.

642
00:40:32,017 --> 00:40:34,103
Anyway, we're really sorry.

643
00:40:38,107 --> 00:40:39,442
Right? You're sorry.

644
00:40:39,525 --> 00:40:41,902
They just don't know the full story.

645
00:40:42,528 --> 00:40:46,323
Exactly. We only read about how you were ruined.

646
00:40:46,866 --> 00:40:50,828
-Right? -But still, we didn't believe the media.

647
00:40:50,911 --> 00:40:52,788
"No way. They'll probably still prosper

648
00:40:52,872 --> 00:40:54,582
-for another three years." -That's right.

649
00:40:54,665 --> 00:40:56,834
-Yes. -We wanted to check the facts.

650
00:40:56,917 --> 00:40:59,253
And share the truth.

651
00:41:00,880 --> 00:41:01,755
I understand.

652
00:41:01,839 --> 00:41:03,257
I'm at fault too.

653
00:41:03,340 --> 00:41:04,842
I should've told you I was here.

654
00:41:04,925 --> 00:41:06,510
-I was only listening in. -I'm relieved.

655
00:41:06,594 --> 00:41:11,015
We'll be seeing each other often, so I'm glad we reconciled.

656
00:41:11,098 --> 00:41:12,641
That's right.

657
00:41:13,392 --> 00:41:14,560
It won't be for that long.

658
00:41:14,643 --> 00:41:16,479
We're just taking a break.

659
00:41:16,562 --> 00:41:18,564
We're only here to rest.

660
00:41:18,647 --> 00:41:23,777
We've been to places like Bali, Hawaii, and Cancún way too often.

661
00:41:24,653 --> 00:41:28,616
So we thought we'd visit an unusual place this time.

662
00:41:31,118 --> 00:41:31,952
"Unusual"?

663
00:41:32,870 --> 00:41:35,331
Compared to Cancún? Definitely.

664
00:41:35,414 --> 00:41:37,541
Yongdu-ri is unique, and there's no ocean either.

665
00:41:38,542 --> 00:41:42,421
It's a bit uncomfortable, but I think this is a good experience.

666
00:41:42,505 --> 00:41:45,633
When will I get to stay at a place like this ever again?

667
00:41:45,716 --> 00:41:48,385
No amount of money can buy this experience.

668
00:41:48,469 --> 00:41:50,596
Right, and you're broke too.

669
00:41:52,139 --> 00:41:53,974
-Sorry? -It's true that you're poor for now.

670
00:41:54,058 --> 00:41:56,018
Their assets are frozen, right?

671
00:41:56,101 --> 00:41:58,771
Yes, but they'll get them later.

672
00:41:58,854 --> 00:42:01,148
Right, but they don't know

673
00:42:01,232 --> 00:42:04,151
if they'll still be alive by then.

674
00:42:04,235 --> 00:42:07,196
Our family owns 50,000 pyeongs' worth of land that's been a green belt

675
00:42:07,279 --> 00:42:08,405
for 50 years.

676
00:42:08,489 --> 00:42:09,323
Exactly.

677
00:42:11,700 --> 00:42:12,535
All right, then.

678
00:42:12,618 --> 00:42:16,956
How about you guys all leave now that you've reconciled?

679
00:42:17,790 --> 00:42:20,584
I've never seen anyone leave our town

680
00:42:20,668 --> 00:42:23,671
after saying that they would.

681
00:42:24,171 --> 00:42:26,632
Excuse me, but what are you getting at?

682
00:42:26,715 --> 00:42:28,551
I just have a hunch

683
00:42:28,634 --> 00:42:31,929
that we'll be seeing each other often for a very long time.

684
00:42:32,012 --> 00:42:33,180
And I'm happy about that.

685
00:42:34,807 --> 00:42:36,350
Let's go then.

686
00:42:36,433 --> 00:42:37,851
-Go? -Yes, go.

687
00:42:37,935 --> 00:42:39,687
-Right now? -Yes, right now.

688
00:42:39,770 --> 00:42:41,605
-Bye. -We're going now.

689
00:42:42,439 --> 00:42:43,440
What…

690
00:42:44,608 --> 00:42:45,859
Goodness.

691
00:42:46,527 --> 00:42:47,611
I'm so stressed.

692
00:42:48,320 --> 00:42:49,154
Caffeine.

693
00:42:49,989 --> 00:42:50,823
Caffeine!

694
00:42:54,618 --> 00:42:58,122
JUNE'S GARDEN

695
00:42:58,205 --> 00:42:59,790
PLEASE PAY IN ADVANCE

696
00:43:17,600 --> 00:43:20,519
I'd like to order.

697
00:43:21,770 --> 00:43:22,771
Please take my order.

698
00:43:22,855 --> 00:43:25,107
We take orders up here.

699
00:43:33,324 --> 00:43:34,617
Two shots of espresso.

700
00:43:36,327 --> 00:43:37,494
That'll be 3,200 won.

701
00:43:37,578 --> 00:43:39,538
-Do you have an affiliated card? -It's okay.

702
00:43:39,622 --> 00:43:40,456
Here.

703
00:43:45,753 --> 00:43:46,837
It doesn't work.

704
00:43:53,052 --> 00:43:54,470
How will you pay, ma'am?

705
00:43:56,847 --> 00:44:00,059
Look. I'm in dire need of some coffee.

706
00:44:00,142 --> 00:44:03,520
Can I drink some first, then pay you later?

707
00:44:04,146 --> 00:44:05,981
Drink first, pay later.

708
00:44:07,441 --> 00:44:08,484
May I do that?

709
00:44:08,567 --> 00:44:11,779
I'm sorry, but there's a line.

710
00:44:11,862 --> 00:44:13,072
Could you step aside?

711
00:44:18,118 --> 00:44:19,161
Hello.

712
00:44:19,244 --> 00:44:20,704
Ten iced Americanos,

713
00:44:20,788 --> 00:44:24,041
ten iced lattes, a container of syrup,

714
00:44:24,124 --> 00:44:25,709
and another one full of ice cubes.

715
00:44:25,793 --> 00:44:27,419
-Okay? -Sure. I know.

716
00:44:27,503 --> 00:44:30,839
Also, I'd like to pay for hers too.

717
00:44:30,923 --> 00:44:31,799
Okay.

718
00:44:33,550 --> 00:44:36,428
Why are you having coffee when you can't sleep well?

719
00:44:37,846 --> 00:44:40,683
Anyway, thanks for the coffee.

720
00:44:42,976 --> 00:44:43,852
No need to thank me.

721
00:44:45,062 --> 00:44:46,772
It's not free.

722
00:45:01,704 --> 00:45:03,497
All right, let's begin.

723
00:45:03,580 --> 00:45:05,249
-Okay. -Natasha.

724
00:45:05,332 --> 00:45:06,166
Yes?

725
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:08,419
Be her mentor for the day.

726
00:45:08,502 --> 00:45:09,670
Okay.

727
00:45:13,799 --> 00:45:14,800
Nepotism?

728
00:45:17,511 --> 00:45:19,304
Are you talking to me, young lady?

729
00:45:19,388 --> 00:45:21,932
Yes, I'm talking to you.

730
00:45:22,015 --> 00:45:24,560
Why are you speaking casually? I'm older than you.

731
00:45:24,643 --> 00:45:26,603
I'm not a young lady. I'm your senior.

732
00:45:26,687 --> 00:45:27,938
Do you know what that means?

733
00:45:28,021 --> 00:45:30,441
Yes, times have changed.

734
00:45:30,524 --> 00:45:33,819
I didn't even dare to step on my seniors' shadows back in the day.

735
00:45:33,902 --> 00:45:35,654
What? What shadow?

736
00:45:35,738 --> 00:45:37,114
Is she a boomer or what?

737
00:45:37,197 --> 00:45:39,074
Do you not want to learn? Forget it.

738
00:45:39,658 --> 00:45:41,493
Fine. What am I supposed to do?

739
00:45:41,577 --> 00:45:42,828
Follow me.

740
00:45:43,454 --> 00:45:44,288
Hurry up.

741
00:45:44,872 --> 00:45:45,706
Come on.

742
00:45:45,789 --> 00:45:47,416
I'll only demonstrate once.

743
00:45:48,041 --> 00:45:49,918
Do this. Then this.

744
00:45:50,002 --> 00:45:52,296
Then like this.

745
00:45:53,422 --> 00:45:54,590
Your turn.

746
00:46:00,596 --> 00:46:01,805
Like this?

747
00:46:01,889 --> 00:46:03,974
Hold this part.

748
00:46:04,641 --> 00:46:07,019
No, not like that.

749
00:46:07,102 --> 00:46:08,562
You told me to hold it!

750
00:46:08,645 --> 00:46:11,565
Is Korean that hard? Do you not understand?

751
00:46:11,648 --> 00:46:14,151
Hold it like this.

752
00:46:18,739 --> 00:46:19,990
Ms. Jeon!

753
00:46:20,073 --> 00:46:22,618
You should fire her. She's a lost cause.

754
00:46:24,453 --> 00:46:27,080
-Jeez. -What? You are.

755
00:46:27,164 --> 00:46:28,749
There sure was nepotism involved.

756
00:46:28,832 --> 00:46:29,958
Gosh!

757
00:46:31,001 --> 00:46:32,127
Look at you.

758
00:46:50,479 --> 00:46:51,855
You didn't get lost.

759
00:46:52,523 --> 00:46:54,233
So? Do you want a hug?

760
00:46:54,316 --> 00:46:55,943
No, thanks. Did you bring it?

761
00:46:57,486 --> 00:46:59,738
You know this is a violation of the labor law, right?

762
00:47:06,411 --> 00:47:08,163
I should be at a farm right now,

763
00:47:08,247 --> 00:47:10,833
baking pizza with organic cheese.

764
00:47:16,213 --> 00:47:17,172
Do you want a hug?

765
00:47:18,048 --> 00:47:19,049
No, thanks.

766
00:47:20,801 --> 00:47:22,261
I just don't get it.

767
00:47:22,344 --> 00:47:24,972
Why did you choose to stay at your former in-laws'?

768
00:47:26,306 --> 00:47:29,643
We were in a rush and just happened to stay here for a bit.

769
00:47:29,726 --> 00:47:31,395
Still, I wouldn't have come here.

770
00:47:31,478 --> 00:47:33,856
Let's say I had to choose between prison and my in-laws.

771
00:47:33,939 --> 00:47:35,983
-I'd choose the former. -No way.

772
00:47:36,483 --> 00:47:39,444
At least I wouldn't have to cook in prison.

773
00:47:40,612 --> 00:47:43,949
My mother-in-law cooks everything. We had japchae and ribs for breakfast.

774
00:47:44,825 --> 00:47:46,451
Gosh, you said "mother-in-law."

775
00:47:47,119 --> 00:47:48,662
Be honest. Is the divorce fake?

776
00:47:48,745 --> 00:47:51,748
-What are you saying? -If not, how could you be so affectionate?

777
00:47:51,832 --> 00:47:54,126
I'm not affectionate. You're mistaken.

778
00:47:54,877 --> 00:47:59,298
Why do you think Mr. Baek is still at work even after the humiliation he received?

779
00:47:59,381 --> 00:48:01,174
What humiliation did he get?

780
00:48:01,800 --> 00:48:03,719
I guess you didn't hear.

781
00:48:03,802 --> 00:48:05,470
I heard on my way here.

782
00:48:05,554 --> 00:48:07,639
He's waiting to be reassigned.

783
00:48:07,723 --> 00:48:09,808
Waiting to be reassigned? What for?

784
00:48:10,851 --> 00:48:12,895
Some malpractice or something.

785
00:48:12,978 --> 00:48:15,105
They'll hold a personnel committee soon.

786
00:48:17,065 --> 00:48:18,150
Malpractice?

787
00:48:18,984 --> 00:48:19,818
What kind?

788
00:48:20,485 --> 00:48:22,905
The Audit Team couldn't find anything on him.

789
00:48:22,988 --> 00:48:25,365
He received bribes from a law firm.

790
00:48:25,449 --> 00:48:26,533
What?

791
00:48:26,617 --> 00:48:27,784
Hold on.

792
00:48:27,868 --> 00:48:29,620
Did he embezzle money from labor costs?

793
00:48:29,703 --> 00:48:32,372
He gave a rival company a list of our VIP customers.

794
00:48:32,456 --> 00:48:34,291
There are many more that I can come up with.

795
00:48:34,374 --> 00:48:36,960
So you're going to make false accusations?

796
00:48:37,836 --> 00:48:38,670
Is that it?

797
00:48:39,713 --> 00:48:42,132
I'm debating which one to use.

798
00:48:42,215 --> 00:48:45,344
But whatever it is, he'll become an ex-convict.

799
00:48:53,101 --> 00:48:55,479
Hey, you're coming home together.

800
00:48:55,562 --> 00:48:56,688
Right.

801
00:48:57,522 --> 00:49:00,817
I had an appointment in Seoul.

802
00:49:04,279 --> 00:49:05,113
Hey.

803
00:49:06,907 --> 00:49:08,200
I thought long and hard.

804
00:49:08,283 --> 00:49:09,826
-"Should I tell him this?" -Then don't.

805
00:49:09,910 --> 00:49:12,204
Do you know who came by last night?

806
00:49:12,287 --> 00:49:13,121
I do.

807
00:49:13,914 --> 00:49:17,000
You do? So you know Yoon Eun-sung visited Hae-in.

808
00:49:17,084 --> 00:49:18,001
I do.

809
00:49:19,044 --> 00:49:22,005
But why did he secretly visit her in the middle of the night?

810
00:49:22,089 --> 00:49:23,924
Is something going on between them?

811
00:49:24,007 --> 00:49:26,093
Don't be ridiculous.

812
00:49:26,176 --> 00:49:27,886
Don't snap at me.

813
00:49:28,637 --> 00:49:31,640
I didn't snap at you, and there's nothing going on.

814
00:49:31,723 --> 00:49:33,642
There's absolutely nothing going on.

815
00:49:33,725 --> 00:49:34,935
You don't know anything.

816
00:49:37,354 --> 00:49:39,272
What's his problem?

817
00:49:40,857 --> 00:49:41,692
No way.

818
00:49:42,442 --> 00:49:43,944
Is he jealous?

819
00:49:44,027 --> 00:49:46,780
Hae-in didn't even budge after hearing about So-yeong.

820
00:49:47,280 --> 00:49:48,365
But Hyun-woo…

821
00:49:48,448 --> 00:49:49,741
Gosh.

822
00:49:49,825 --> 00:49:50,867
What an idiot.

823
00:49:51,493 --> 00:49:52,327
Jeez.

824
00:49:54,204 --> 00:49:56,123
Great job today!

825
00:49:56,206 --> 00:49:57,124
Thank you!

826
00:49:57,833 --> 00:50:00,544
-Let's start with Natasha. -Okay.

827
00:50:00,627 --> 00:50:03,755
You picked 4,000 which makes the total 280,000 won.

828
00:50:03,839 --> 00:50:05,757
But I'll give you 300,000 won.

829
00:50:07,801 --> 00:50:10,429
As for you, you picked 70 which makes

830
00:50:10,512 --> 00:50:12,014
the total 4,900 won.

831
00:50:12,097 --> 00:50:14,766
You owe me coffee, so you'll get 1,700 in total.

832
00:50:14,850 --> 00:50:17,019
-Ms. Lee Su-gyeong? -Here.

833
00:50:17,102 --> 00:50:18,812
-Good work. -Thank you!

834
00:50:18,895 --> 00:50:20,105
-Ms. Park Seon-nyeo? -Here.

835
00:50:20,188 --> 00:50:21,064
-Great job. -Goodness.

836
00:50:44,087 --> 00:50:46,298
Honey, here are your sleeping pills.

837
00:51:00,395 --> 00:51:02,481
Goodness, honey.

838
00:51:02,564 --> 00:51:05,942
You haven't slept so well without any medication in a long time.

839
00:51:39,267 --> 00:51:42,104
Why are you drinking alone at this hour?

840
00:51:42,187 --> 00:51:43,021
Well…

841
00:51:43,647 --> 00:51:45,982
I feel gloomy now that I've stepped down from my position.

842
00:51:46,066 --> 00:51:49,194
I was only the village head of this tiny neighborhood.

843
00:51:56,993 --> 00:51:58,912
I can understand.

844
00:51:58,995 --> 00:51:59,830
Gosh.

845
00:52:00,330 --> 00:52:01,957
-Really? -Take a look.

846
00:52:03,125 --> 00:52:05,877
My battery is still half full at this hour

847
00:52:05,961 --> 00:52:07,045
since no one has called me.

848
00:52:08,088 --> 00:52:09,464
I see.

849
00:52:09,548 --> 00:52:10,924
No one's picking up either.

850
00:52:11,007 --> 00:52:15,053
When I used to be the vice-chairman, I almost never heard the message

851
00:52:15,137 --> 00:52:17,556
that played when you didn't pick up.

852
00:52:17,639 --> 00:52:19,391
But I hear it every day now.

853
00:52:23,270 --> 00:52:24,146
Gosh.

854
00:52:24,646 --> 00:52:26,523
This is the end of our reign.

855
00:52:28,233 --> 00:52:31,736
I agree with the saying that even your shadow abandons you

856
00:52:31,820 --> 00:52:32,988
in dark times.

857
00:52:41,496 --> 00:52:42,455
Goodness.

858
00:52:47,586 --> 00:52:49,004
Do you have any makgeolli?

859
00:52:50,213 --> 00:52:52,966
Father! You said Chemicals and Motors were mine.

860
00:52:53,049 --> 00:52:54,092
Then break up with her.

861
00:52:54,176 --> 00:52:57,721
If not, you'll never get my companies!

862
00:52:57,804 --> 00:52:59,848
No, I refuse to break up with her.

863
00:52:59,931 --> 00:53:01,183
What did you say?

864
00:53:01,266 --> 00:53:02,851
-Never. -How dare you?

865
00:53:02,934 --> 00:53:04,811
Stop! Stop right there!

866
00:53:04,895 --> 00:53:08,440
CEO JANG AND HIS THREE SONS

867
00:53:08,523 --> 00:53:09,649
Come on, now.

868
00:53:10,483 --> 00:53:12,485
They always end it at the best parts.

869
00:53:12,569 --> 00:53:13,403
Goodness.

870
00:53:14,988 --> 00:53:16,364
Do they really do that?

871
00:53:17,616 --> 00:53:18,450
Sorry?

872
00:53:18,533 --> 00:53:20,994
Is that how the rich live?

873
00:53:22,120 --> 00:53:23,079
I beg to differ.

874
00:53:23,163 --> 00:53:25,332
Those dramas make me think

875
00:53:25,415 --> 00:53:28,293
the writers didn't do their research properly.

876
00:53:28,376 --> 00:53:29,377
How come?

877
00:53:30,253 --> 00:53:32,964
The characters are often seen grabbing their necks.

878
00:53:33,048 --> 00:53:37,093
But the rich are very strict about their blood pressure.

879
00:53:37,177 --> 00:53:41,056
-After all, we have a live-in doctor. -A live-in doctor?

880
00:53:41,139 --> 00:53:44,267
They remove sodium from our diet if our blood pressure rises even a bit.

881
00:53:44,351 --> 00:53:45,852
They remove it all.

882
00:53:47,229 --> 00:53:50,649
And the houses all have stairs in the living room.

883
00:53:50,732 --> 00:53:54,236
Exactly. You don't all have them, do you?

884
00:53:54,319 --> 00:53:55,820
It's not the Opera House.

885
00:53:55,904 --> 00:53:59,658
We all do, and we often use them to go upstairs.

886
00:53:59,741 --> 00:54:02,994
But we take the elevator when going down to protect our knees.

887
00:54:03,912 --> 00:54:07,374
The writers need to do better research.

888
00:54:12,420 --> 00:54:13,630
This is just right.

889
00:54:28,812 --> 00:54:30,105
Are you sleeping?

890
00:54:39,614 --> 00:54:41,283
Hae-in, are you asleep?

891
00:54:51,793 --> 00:54:52,627
What is it?

892
00:54:54,796 --> 00:54:55,964
Say what you need to say.

893
00:54:59,342 --> 00:55:01,177
I heard Eun-sung came by yesterday.

894
00:55:01,886 --> 00:55:03,054
Did Soo-cheol tell you?

895
00:55:03,138 --> 00:55:04,723
That's not important.

896
00:55:06,558 --> 00:55:07,559
What did he say?

897
00:55:08,268 --> 00:55:10,312
He just asked why I was here.

898
00:55:12,188 --> 00:55:13,273
What's it to him?

899
00:55:14,649 --> 00:55:15,483
What else?

900
00:55:15,567 --> 00:55:16,568
He also told me

901
00:55:17,193 --> 00:55:18,361
to work again

902
00:55:18,945 --> 00:55:19,988
and come home.

903
00:55:20,071 --> 00:55:21,323
Come home?

904
00:55:21,406 --> 00:55:22,449
Yes.

905
00:55:22,532 --> 00:55:25,285
Will he move out if you do?

906
00:55:26,953 --> 00:55:28,621
He'll stay?

907
00:55:28,705 --> 00:55:29,539
Well…

908
00:55:30,040 --> 00:55:31,958
We didn't talk in detail.

909
00:55:32,042 --> 00:55:34,127
Does he want to live with you?

910
00:55:34,210 --> 00:55:35,628
You two aren't together.

911
00:55:35,712 --> 00:55:37,339
Neither are we, but look at us.

912
00:55:37,422 --> 00:55:39,674
No, we're different. We were…

913
00:55:42,427 --> 00:55:44,304
married.

914
00:55:44,387 --> 00:55:45,680
But not anymore.

915
00:55:47,098 --> 00:55:50,143
You've helped me so far, and I think you've done enough.

916
00:55:51,644 --> 00:55:52,562
What are you saying?

917
00:55:52,645 --> 00:55:54,522
I heard you're waiting to be assigned.

918
00:55:55,273 --> 00:55:56,316
Why didn't you tell me?

919
00:55:57,525 --> 00:55:58,401
It's nothing.

920
00:55:58,485 --> 00:56:00,653
How is it nothing when the reason is malpractice?

921
00:56:00,737 --> 00:56:02,906
Who knows on what documents they forged your signature?

922
00:56:02,989 --> 00:56:05,492
Embezzlement? Something illegal? He's capable of anything.

923
00:56:05,575 --> 00:56:07,660
You're in no position to worry about me.

924
00:56:07,744 --> 00:56:10,205
You didn't want to worry about me.

925
00:56:11,247 --> 00:56:12,665
Same goes for me.

926
00:56:14,709 --> 00:56:16,336
I'll take care of my own issues.

927
00:56:18,713 --> 00:56:20,131
I feel uncomfortable

928
00:56:20,215 --> 00:56:22,342
that you're suffering uselessly because of me.

929
00:56:27,680 --> 00:56:29,974
Don't be so cold.

930
00:56:31,351 --> 00:56:32,936
I'm just doing it for you--

931
00:56:33,019 --> 00:56:34,729
Don't do anything for me.

932
00:56:37,440 --> 00:56:39,734
I'll find my own solutions.

933
00:57:52,724 --> 00:57:53,850
Hello, Doctor.

934
00:57:54,476 --> 00:57:56,895
Yes, I'm taking the medication.

935
00:57:57,687 --> 00:58:00,231
But I've been getting a lot of headaches lately.

936
00:58:00,815 --> 00:58:03,610
I've been giving myself the WBC injection every day.

937
00:58:06,029 --> 00:58:09,699
The tumor didn't seem to have grown in the latest photos.

938
00:58:09,782 --> 00:58:11,284
Could it be something else?

939
00:58:13,077 --> 00:58:13,912
Hyun-woo.

940
00:58:13,995 --> 00:58:15,079
Wake up.

941
00:58:16,247 --> 00:58:17,207
Wake up right now.

942
00:58:20,001 --> 00:58:21,002
What is it?

943
00:58:21,836 --> 00:58:23,838
Tell me the truth.

944
00:58:23,922 --> 00:58:26,549
Hae-in is sick, isn't she?

945
00:58:28,760 --> 00:58:31,346
Tell me. She's been acting strange lately.

946
00:58:31,429 --> 00:58:33,014
She also fainted last time.

947
00:58:33,097 --> 00:58:35,225
I think she's injecting herself too.

948
00:58:35,308 --> 00:58:37,018
I think something is up.

949
00:58:40,772 --> 00:58:43,483
She wants it to be a secret.

950
00:58:45,318 --> 00:58:46,152
But…

951
00:58:47,737 --> 00:58:50,823
I need you to take care of her when I'm away,

952
00:58:50,907 --> 00:58:52,158
so I'll confide in you.

953
00:58:52,242 --> 00:58:53,326
What is it?

954
00:59:01,251 --> 00:59:02,252
She has…

955
00:59:04,921 --> 00:59:06,005
a brain tumor.

956
00:59:08,841 --> 00:59:09,676
But…

957
00:59:10,426 --> 00:59:11,761
it's big,

958
00:59:13,846 --> 00:59:15,139
and it's a rare case.

959
00:59:16,182 --> 00:59:18,393
So she can't get surgery right now.

960
00:59:18,476 --> 00:59:21,145
She's monitoring it while taking medication.

961
00:59:28,736 --> 00:59:29,737
But the rate

962
00:59:30,405 --> 00:59:31,614
isn't high.

963
00:59:33,825 --> 00:59:34,701
What rate?

964
00:59:35,326 --> 00:59:36,786
Do you mean

965
00:59:38,162 --> 00:59:40,123
the survival rate?

966
00:59:51,593 --> 00:59:53,386
Goodness.

967
00:59:53,469 --> 00:59:54,637
I can't believe this.

968
00:59:55,263 --> 00:59:56,806
She's still so young.

969
00:59:57,307 --> 00:59:59,058
No one in her family knows

970
00:59:59,517 --> 01:00:00,727
except for her aunt.

971
01:00:01,936 --> 01:00:03,354
Not even her parents?

972
01:00:04,439 --> 01:00:05,315
No.

973
01:00:06,482 --> 01:00:09,444
They should still know about this.

974
01:00:10,403 --> 01:00:11,988
When did you find out?

975
01:00:16,743 --> 01:00:19,245
Do you remember that day when I visited

976
01:00:20,246 --> 01:00:22,248
and said I wanted to divorce her?

977
01:00:23,082 --> 01:00:25,376
I found out that day after returning to Seoul.

978
01:00:28,212 --> 01:00:29,547
What do you mean?

979
01:00:29,631 --> 01:00:30,840
So…

980
01:00:31,799 --> 01:00:34,719
you were determined to divorce her,

981
01:00:34,802 --> 01:00:37,180
then suddenly had a change of heart because…

982
01:00:43,019 --> 01:00:43,853
Yes.

983
01:00:45,104 --> 01:00:49,901
After finding out about it, I had decided to maintain our marriage.

984
01:00:55,823 --> 01:00:57,241
You scumbag.

985
01:00:57,325 --> 01:00:58,534
You should know better.

986
01:01:00,119 --> 01:01:00,995
Oh, dear.

987
01:01:01,871 --> 01:01:03,206
I had no idea

988
01:01:04,374 --> 01:01:05,917
and only pitied you.

989
01:01:08,002 --> 01:01:09,921
How could you?

990
01:01:12,632 --> 01:01:13,591
I know.

991
01:01:15,635 --> 01:01:17,428
I'm a scumbag.

992
01:01:17,512 --> 01:01:22,517
Hae-in found out about everything yet still came here when I told her to.

993
01:01:25,478 --> 01:01:26,479
So, Mom…

994
01:01:29,941 --> 01:01:31,150
please take…

995
01:01:33,152 --> 01:01:34,112
good care of her

996
01:01:35,613 --> 01:01:36,906
when I'm away.

997
01:01:38,700 --> 01:01:39,575
I beg you.

998
01:02:29,625 --> 01:02:30,460
Mom.

999
01:02:37,592 --> 01:02:38,426
What is it?

1000
01:02:39,051 --> 01:02:40,803
I came by for some kimchi.

1001
01:02:40,887 --> 01:02:43,264
Your mom is crying.

1002
01:02:44,682 --> 01:02:46,893
-Why? -Isn't it obvious?

1003
01:02:46,976 --> 01:02:50,021
She was always against it and wanted me to quit.

1004
01:02:50,104 --> 01:02:53,941
But now that I've stepped down, she must be upset.

1005
01:02:54,025 --> 01:02:57,653
What? She said she was relieved that you were no longer the village head.

1006
01:03:00,031 --> 01:03:01,616
She didn't mean it.

1007
01:03:01,699 --> 01:03:02,992
Goodness.

1008
01:03:03,075 --> 01:03:03,910
Mom.

1009
01:03:03,993 --> 01:03:06,496
Just go. Come back later.

1010
01:03:08,998 --> 01:03:10,583
This is a feast.

1011
01:03:11,209 --> 01:03:12,835
I should just eat here today.

1012
01:03:13,419 --> 01:03:15,129
Tell Hae-in to come and eat.

1013
01:03:16,130 --> 01:03:17,006
Okay.

1014
01:03:22,220 --> 01:03:23,179
Honey.

1015
01:03:23,846 --> 01:03:25,389
What's with you? Move.

1016
01:03:26,599 --> 01:03:28,768
I know what you're going through.

1017
01:03:29,977 --> 01:03:30,812
But…

1018
01:03:31,312 --> 01:03:32,146
you see…

1019
01:03:34,065 --> 01:03:35,566
Why don't you think like this?

1020
01:03:36,776 --> 01:03:40,238
I, Baek Du-gwan, used to belong to the people.

1021
01:03:40,863 --> 01:03:43,741
But now, I'm all yours.

1022
01:03:45,201 --> 01:03:47,495
Why would I ever want that?

1023
01:03:49,705 --> 01:03:50,998
Is that so?

1024
01:03:55,753 --> 01:03:58,464
Goodness, we're feasting for breakfast.

1025
01:03:59,715 --> 01:04:00,716
What's the occasion?

1026
01:04:01,759 --> 01:04:03,261
Please help yourselves.

1027
01:04:10,309 --> 01:04:12,311
Hae-in, come and eat.

1028
01:04:12,395 --> 01:04:13,229
Okay.

1029
01:04:18,234 --> 01:04:19,902
Where's your sister?

1030
01:04:19,986 --> 01:04:23,114
Beom-ja left for Seoul in the morning to run some errands.

1031
01:04:23,197 --> 01:04:24,073
I see.

1032
01:04:24,156 --> 01:04:27,368
Gosh, it would've been nice had she eaten with us.

1033
01:04:27,451 --> 01:04:29,287
Let's eat.

1034
01:04:43,926 --> 01:04:46,512
By the way, where's Soo-cheol?

1035
01:04:54,604 --> 01:04:56,606
QUEEN'S BOXING GYM

1036
01:04:56,689 --> 01:04:57,732
GEONUMAMA HAS LOGGED IN

1037
01:05:01,986 --> 01:05:04,113
Da-hye.

1038
01:05:12,079 --> 01:05:13,497
-Da-hye. -Gosh.

1039
01:05:13,581 --> 01:05:15,499
Why is he playing this?

1040
01:05:15,583 --> 01:05:17,418
I kept my character because of all the items.

1041
01:05:17,501 --> 01:05:19,337
-Jeez. -Let me just say one thing.

1042
01:05:19,420 --> 01:05:21,047
Forget it. You'll just swear at me.

1043
01:05:21,130 --> 01:05:22,173
GEONUPAPA SENT A MESSAGE

1044
01:05:22,256 --> 01:05:23,591
What is this?

1045
01:05:23,674 --> 01:05:26,302
This is Geon-u's vaccination record in English and Korean.

1046
01:05:26,385 --> 01:05:29,263
He needs his second round of MMR vaccine and chicken pox vaccine.

1047
01:05:29,347 --> 01:05:31,599
Make sure he gets them wherever you are.

1048
01:05:31,682 --> 01:05:34,560
Make sure you sing "Baby Shark" when he gets them.

1049
01:05:35,186 --> 01:05:43,319
Baby shark, doo doo doo doo doo doo Baby shark

1050
01:05:43,402 --> 01:05:49,784
Mommy Shark, doo doo doo doo doo doo

1051
01:05:49,867 --> 01:05:51,786
All done.

1052
01:05:51,869 --> 01:05:53,120
-Thank you. -Gosh.

1053
01:05:53,204 --> 01:05:54,747
Gosh, Geon-u.

1054
01:05:54,830 --> 01:05:56,248
Did it hurt?

1055
01:05:56,332 --> 01:05:57,249
Well done.

1056
01:05:57,333 --> 01:05:59,502
He didn't even cry.

1057
01:06:02,171 --> 01:06:03,005
Come on.

1058
01:06:18,479 --> 01:06:20,690
GEONUMAMA HAS LOGGED OUT

1059
01:06:46,382 --> 01:06:47,800
Going somewhere?

1060
01:06:48,634 --> 01:06:50,011
-Seoul. -All of a sudden?

1061
01:06:52,304 --> 01:06:53,264
Look.

1062
01:06:53,347 --> 01:06:56,600
Even Beom-ja left for Seoul. Why are you all going there?

1063
01:06:56,684 --> 01:07:00,062
Do you want the reporters to see you? We're in hiding, you know?

1064
01:07:00,980 --> 01:07:02,648
There's something I must do.

1065
01:07:03,399 --> 01:07:04,817
I heard Eun-sung visited.

1066
01:07:06,527 --> 01:07:09,321
What kind of plans are you having Soo-cheol keep secret?

1067
01:07:09,405 --> 01:07:11,449
Are you going to meet him today too?

1068
01:07:12,533 --> 01:07:16,287
For what? Are you going to beg him to spare at least you?

1069
01:07:18,289 --> 01:07:19,415
Of course, I should.

1070
01:07:20,374 --> 01:07:21,876
Should we all go down together?

1071
01:07:22,376 --> 01:07:24,628
What? I can't believe you.

1072
01:07:26,297 --> 01:07:28,382
Don't tell me you'll work for him.

1073
01:07:28,466 --> 01:07:30,634
That was my spot from the get-go.

1074
01:07:33,054 --> 01:07:36,265
Don't tell me you two colluded so you could kick your family out

1075
01:07:36,348 --> 01:07:39,643
and take over the company all by yourself.

1076
01:07:46,859 --> 01:07:48,527
Think however you want.

1077
01:07:48,611 --> 01:07:49,612
Hey!

1078
01:08:06,670 --> 01:08:08,339
Sweetie, are you going to Seoul?

1079
01:08:08,422 --> 01:08:09,256
Yes.

1080
01:08:09,840 --> 01:08:12,176
You won't get any taxis here.

1081
01:08:12,259 --> 01:08:13,469
I'll drive you. Hop on.

1082
01:08:20,810 --> 01:08:21,644
Hold tight.

1083
01:08:35,783 --> 01:08:36,617
Mother.

1084
01:08:36,700 --> 01:08:37,827
Yes?

1085
01:08:38,953 --> 01:08:41,038
Thank you for everything.

1086
01:08:42,873 --> 01:08:46,085
Are you going somewhere far away? That's odd for you to say.

1087
01:09:00,683 --> 01:09:02,518
The wind must be strong.

1088
01:09:03,602 --> 01:09:04,979
My eyes are getting watery.

1089
01:09:16,866 --> 01:09:19,326
Of course. I know this is forbidden.

1090
01:09:22,454 --> 01:09:26,375
But we've never kept any secrets from each other.

1091
01:09:26,458 --> 01:09:29,670
Remember when your youngest son fled to Sokcho because he couldn't forget

1092
01:09:29,753 --> 01:09:32,840
his first love and I went there to get him?

1093
01:09:32,923 --> 01:09:34,717
We can laugh about it now.

1094
01:09:34,800 --> 01:09:36,886
He was in so much pain.

1095
01:09:36,969 --> 01:09:38,137
Las Vegas, was it?

1096
01:09:38,220 --> 01:09:40,723
He went there to do drugs--

1097
01:09:43,100 --> 01:09:44,727
Exactly.

1098
01:09:45,519 --> 01:09:47,062
So will you tell me?

1099
01:09:47,146 --> 01:09:49,565
Of course. No one will know that you told me.

1100
01:09:54,361 --> 01:09:55,362
Who?

1101
01:09:57,448 --> 01:09:59,825
I see. Chairman Hong Man-dae from Queens?

1102
01:10:00,618 --> 01:10:04,038
So that's where he is.

1103
01:10:52,628 --> 01:10:54,713
Does Mr. Baek know that Ms. Hong is here?

1104
01:10:54,797 --> 01:10:55,631
I don't think so.

1105
01:10:55,714 --> 01:10:57,716
Right, she left him.

1106
01:11:03,806 --> 01:11:06,475
-Where are you rushing to? -As you know, it's an emergency.

1107
01:11:06,558 --> 01:11:07,726
What's going on?

1108
01:11:08,352 --> 01:11:09,728
You haven't heard.

1109
01:11:09,812 --> 01:11:11,480
Let's keep it that way.

1110
01:11:32,251 --> 01:11:33,544
Welcome back.

1111
01:11:33,627 --> 01:11:35,546
I didn't return because of your threats.

1112
01:11:35,629 --> 01:11:37,631
I know you won't return what was ours.

1113
01:11:37,715 --> 01:11:39,717
So if I can't get it back,

1114
01:11:40,884 --> 01:11:42,594
I guess I'll have to share.

1115
01:11:49,310 --> 01:11:50,394
So keep your word.

1116
01:12:23,302 --> 01:12:25,846
The press conference will begin soon.

1117
01:12:25,929 --> 01:12:28,682
Like we mentioned before, we won't answer any questions.

1118
01:12:33,812 --> 01:12:36,732
PRESS CONFERENCE FOR THE INAUGURATION OF YOON EUN-SUNG AT QUEENS GROUP

1119
01:12:44,323 --> 01:12:45,240
Hae-in.

1120
01:12:45,908 --> 01:12:47,034
How did you know?

1121
01:12:47,534 --> 01:12:48,494
Why are you here?

1122
01:12:50,496 --> 01:12:51,330
I told you.

1123
01:12:52,039 --> 01:12:53,415
I'll find my own solutions.

1124
01:12:53,499 --> 01:12:54,666
And this…

1125
01:12:59,922 --> 01:13:01,173
-is your solution? -Yes.

1126
01:13:02,257 --> 01:13:04,426
I like things to be certain and quick.

1127
01:13:05,969 --> 01:13:07,679
Let's go. It's almost time.

1128
01:13:35,958 --> 01:13:37,668
-Are you sure this is it? -I'm telling you.

1129
01:13:37,751 --> 01:13:40,170
I double-checked. I'm positive.

1130
01:13:45,551 --> 01:13:46,468
MS. MOH SEUL-HEE

1131
01:13:52,099 --> 01:13:54,059
-Hello, ma'am. -Have you found him yet?

1132
01:13:54,143 --> 01:13:58,313
No, ma'am. I searched all throughout Seoul.

1133
01:13:58,397 --> 01:14:01,191
Maybe he's in a rural area.

1134
01:14:03,610 --> 01:14:05,070
Of course.

1135
01:14:05,154 --> 01:14:07,448
I'll call you as soon as I find him.

1136
01:14:09,408 --> 01:14:11,952
Did you see that? I turned my back on her.

1137
01:14:26,967 --> 01:14:29,303
Yes, his condition is the same.

1138
01:14:29,386 --> 01:14:30,220
Yes.

1139
01:14:38,604 --> 01:14:40,606
The major economic newspapers, dailies,

1140
01:14:40,689 --> 01:14:43,567
live media, and ones overseas have made additional requests,

1141
01:14:43,650 --> 01:14:45,444
so we're getting them in order.

1142
01:14:45,527 --> 01:14:47,321
The PR Team has already handed out a guide.

1143
01:14:48,405 --> 01:14:50,532
You can follow this guide, and we'll release it

1144
01:14:50,616 --> 01:14:51,909
without an embargo.

1145
01:14:52,493 --> 01:14:55,871
We'll have a teleprompter, so you can relax and read the words.

1146
01:14:56,455 --> 01:14:58,540
What about your wedding announcement?

1147
01:14:59,458 --> 01:15:00,918
Don't include that.

1148
01:15:01,001 --> 01:15:03,045
I'll announce it at the end.

1149
01:15:03,128 --> 01:15:04,087
Yes, sir.

1150
01:15:06,673 --> 01:15:07,674
Is that okay?

1151
01:15:30,489 --> 01:15:32,533
Hello, I'm Yoon Eun-sung.

1152
01:15:34,326 --> 01:15:37,621
Pione Investment has become Queens' second biggest shareholder.

1153
01:15:37,704 --> 01:15:39,540
And I became the new chairman of Queens Group

1154
01:15:39,623 --> 01:15:42,167
after holding an extraordinary general meeting.

1155
01:15:42,251 --> 01:15:45,212
This decision was inevitable since the former chairman fell ill,

1156
01:15:45,295 --> 01:15:48,131
and we had to stop the fall of our stocks.

1157
01:15:48,215 --> 01:15:52,511
In addition, I've had a lot of experience in saving companies

1158
01:15:52,594 --> 01:15:55,264
from crises and restabilizing them.

1159
01:15:55,347 --> 01:15:56,807
Despite everything, however,

1160
01:15:56,890 --> 01:15:59,434
I was tormented by groundless assumptions

1161
01:15:59,518 --> 01:16:01,061
and fake accusations

1162
01:16:01,687 --> 01:16:03,605
about how I betrayed the former chairman,

1163
01:16:03,689 --> 01:16:05,732
kicked out his family,

1164
01:16:05,816 --> 01:16:10,445
stole from them, confined them, and stowed them away in Southeast Asia.

1165
01:16:14,283 --> 01:16:16,410
One thing for sure is

1166
01:16:16,493 --> 01:16:18,579
this was exactly what the former chairman wanted.

1167
01:16:19,288 --> 01:16:22,124
To prove this and clear up the misunderstandings,

1168
01:16:22,207 --> 01:16:25,252
I'd like to make a big announcement today.

1169
01:16:29,881 --> 01:16:32,884
I will reappoint Ms. Hong Hae-in, my longtime friend

1170
01:16:33,468 --> 01:16:36,388
and talented businesswoman, as the CEO of Queens Department Store.

1171
01:16:37,222 --> 01:16:39,683
During the past three years, the store made

1172
01:16:39,766 --> 01:16:41,935
all-time record profits under her management.

1173
01:16:42,019 --> 01:16:44,104
That just shows how competent she is.

1174
01:16:44,187 --> 01:16:46,523
Now, let's hear from her.

1175
01:17:01,204 --> 01:17:03,707
Hello, I'm Hong Hae-in.

1176
01:17:03,790 --> 01:17:06,710
Like Chairman Yoon just said,

1177
01:17:06,793 --> 01:17:10,172
he and I have been friends since university.

1178
01:17:10,255 --> 01:17:12,215
And Mr. Yoon…

1179
01:17:14,468 --> 01:17:16,845
MR. YOON AND I WILL DO OUR BEST TO TAKE A NEW LEAP FORWARD

1180
01:17:16,928 --> 01:17:17,888
He…

1181
01:17:19,181 --> 01:17:21,600
threatened me.

1182
01:17:30,901 --> 01:17:33,320
He threatened to falsely charge and put Mr. Baek Hyun-woo,

1183
01:17:33,403 --> 01:17:37,699
my husband and former legal director, behind bars.

1184
01:17:37,783 --> 01:17:40,869
I have a recording as proof.

1185
01:17:44,039 --> 01:17:44,873
Wait, Hae-in.

1186
01:17:44,956 --> 01:17:47,709
Furthermore, I can't return to my position

1187
01:17:47,793 --> 01:17:49,336
as the CEO of my department store.

1188
01:17:50,587 --> 01:17:51,713
Because…

1189
01:17:52,547 --> 01:17:54,007
I was told…

1190
01:17:56,259 --> 01:17:59,262
that I have little time left to live.

1191
01:19:07,080 --> 01:19:09,249
Drink up! Bottoms up!

1192
01:19:09,332 --> 01:19:10,959
FOUR YEARS AGO

1193
01:19:11,042 --> 01:19:12,753
Bottoms up!

1194
01:19:12,836 --> 01:19:13,962
Nice!

1195
01:19:15,005 --> 01:19:18,508
Why is our intern, Hae-in, not drinking?

1196
01:19:18,592 --> 01:19:19,885
Drink up!

1197
01:19:20,469 --> 01:19:23,305
I already told you that I wasn't drinking.

1198
01:19:26,558 --> 01:19:30,061
Is that so? Then let's do a love shot.

1199
01:19:30,145 --> 01:19:31,062
Come on.

1200
01:19:31,688 --> 01:19:32,814
Okay. Drink up.

1201
01:19:32,898 --> 01:19:34,816
-Love shot. -Okay. Drink up.

1202
01:19:34,900 --> 01:19:36,985
-Love shot. -Who's that?

1203
01:19:37,861 --> 01:19:39,070
What are you doing?

1204
01:19:39,821 --> 01:19:42,199
I'm drinking instead of her.

1205
01:19:42,282 --> 01:19:43,950
What are you doing?

1206
01:19:44,034 --> 01:19:44,868
What is this?

1207
01:19:55,837 --> 01:19:58,256
Why don't you do the love shot with me?

1208
01:20:16,566 --> 01:20:18,902
Ms. Hong, why are you so upset?

1209
01:20:18,985 --> 01:20:21,154
Did I make you uncomfortable back there?

1210
01:20:21,238 --> 01:20:23,114
Yes, extremely.

1211
01:20:23,198 --> 01:20:24,366
I was just--

1212
01:20:24,449 --> 01:20:25,909
You were just too cute.

1213
01:20:27,369 --> 01:20:29,955
-What? -You're too adorable when you're drunk.

1214
01:20:30,038 --> 01:20:32,123
But you still got drunk and acted cute

1215
01:20:32,207 --> 01:20:33,792
in front of other women.

1216
01:20:34,876 --> 01:20:36,002
How dare you?

1217
01:20:37,712 --> 01:20:38,922
It won't happen again.

1218
01:20:39,005 --> 01:20:39,881
Don't forget.

1219
01:20:39,965 --> 01:20:42,175
You make people's hearts race

1220
01:20:42,717 --> 01:20:43,844
when you're drunk.

1221
01:20:44,636 --> 01:20:46,429
That's your special move.

1222
01:20:46,930 --> 01:20:49,182
So don't do it in front of others.

1223
01:20:49,266 --> 01:20:50,559
Okay.

1224
01:20:57,107 --> 01:20:58,149
I won't do it.

1225
01:21:20,380 --> 01:21:21,840
That's what she said.

1226
01:21:22,883 --> 01:21:23,717
LAST NIGHT

1227
01:21:23,800 --> 01:21:26,261
Hae-in said I made her heart race

1228
01:21:26,970 --> 01:21:27,888
when I got drunk.

1229
01:21:27,971 --> 01:21:28,805
Let's go home.

1230
01:21:28,889 --> 01:21:30,015
You're drunk.

1231
01:21:32,726 --> 01:21:34,519
Do you think she still feels the same way?

1232
01:21:34,603 --> 01:21:37,898
Will her heart still race even now if I got drunk

1233
01:21:38,565 --> 01:21:39,608
and acted cute?

1234
01:21:39,691 --> 01:21:42,527
She wouldn't have divorced you then.

1235
01:21:43,486 --> 01:21:47,240
Why does my heart race when I look at her?

1236
01:21:47,949 --> 01:21:50,577
-It does? -Yes, it does.

1237
01:21:51,953 --> 01:21:56,499
I get butterflies, and I'm happy when I look at her.

1238
01:21:57,751 --> 01:21:59,794
I miss her when she's gone.

1239
01:22:00,921 --> 01:22:02,172
And when I look at her,

1240
01:22:04,925 --> 01:22:06,801
I'm terrified

1241
01:22:08,386 --> 01:22:10,180
that I won't ever see her again.

1242
01:22:10,263 --> 01:22:11,598
Goodness.

1243
01:22:16,811 --> 01:22:18,021
But she doesn't want me…

1244
01:22:20,148 --> 01:22:22,275
to do anything

1245
01:22:23,610 --> 01:22:25,153
for her anymore.

1246
01:22:26,488 --> 01:22:27,739
I make her uncomfortable.

1247
01:22:27,822 --> 01:22:29,324
She must not like you anymore.

1248
01:22:29,991 --> 01:22:32,661
But she put this bandage on me

1249
01:22:34,245 --> 01:22:35,914
and even applied ointment for me.

1250
01:22:36,539 --> 01:22:39,125
Really? Then does she still like you?

1251
01:22:39,209 --> 01:22:40,543
It's confusing.

1252
01:22:41,086 --> 01:22:42,504
Just ask her.

1253
01:22:48,093 --> 01:22:49,844
She likes me.

1254
01:22:51,388 --> 01:22:52,806
She likes me not.

1255
01:22:53,515 --> 01:22:55,350
She likes me.

1256
01:22:56,142 --> 01:22:57,644
She likes me not.

1257
01:22:59,479 --> 01:23:00,897
She likes me.

1258
01:23:04,734 --> 01:23:05,735
She likes me not.

1259
01:23:14,119 --> 01:23:15,286
She likes me.

1260
01:23:16,246 --> 01:23:17,664
She likes me not.

1261
01:23:18,289 --> 01:23:19,874
She likes me.

1262
01:23:20,458 --> 01:23:22,085
She likes me.

1263
01:23:23,586 --> 01:23:24,754
She likes me not.

1264
01:23:26,589 --> 01:23:28,133
She likes me.

1265
01:23:29,467 --> 01:23:30,844
She likes me not.

1266
01:23:31,678 --> 01:23:32,887
She likes me.

1267
01:23:34,014 --> 01:23:35,056
She likes me not.

1268
01:23:36,224 --> 01:23:37,350
She likes me.

1269
01:23:38,768 --> 01:23:39,853
She likes me not.

1270
01:23:46,985 --> 01:23:48,028
She likes me?

1271
01:23:52,490 --> 01:23:53,324
Really?

1272
01:23:58,204 --> 01:23:59,039
Gosh.

1273
01:24:00,457 --> 01:24:03,084
But that's not the case for me.

1274
01:24:05,670 --> 01:24:06,546
I…

1275
01:24:11,301 --> 01:24:12,510
love her.

1276
01:24:32,405 --> 01:24:33,823
I love you, Hae-in.

1277
01:25:06,147 --> 01:25:08,983
QUEEN OF TEARS

1278
01:25:39,639 --> 01:25:41,015
I'll give you anything you want…

1279
01:25:41,766 --> 01:25:43,184
I'll be with her.

1280
01:25:44,477 --> 01:25:48,022
I'm happy as long as you dry my hair with the broken hair dryer.

1281
01:25:48,106 --> 01:25:50,733
Please teach me how to box.

1282
01:25:51,693 --> 01:25:53,903
-Berries? -Shall we meet tonight?

1283
01:25:53,987 --> 01:25:54,946
At night?

1284
01:25:55,029 --> 01:25:56,781
He's looking for the chairman's secret fund.

1285
01:25:56,865 --> 01:25:58,533
I'm going to find it first.

1286
01:25:58,616 --> 01:26:00,160
Get rid

1287
01:26:00,702 --> 01:26:01,744
of Baek Hyun-woo.

1288
01:26:01,828 --> 01:26:03,496
I can't die yet.

1289
01:26:03,580 --> 01:26:05,874
I haven't told you yet.

1290
01:26:05,957 --> 01:26:07,083
I love you.

1291
01:26:12,505 --> 01:26:14,507
Subtitle translation by: Soo-ji Kim
